{
  format: 1
  name: sequence-composition-not-mandated-unspecified
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#evolution", "§20.1"]
  note: '''
    Spec gap around cross-version composition. §20.1: "A runtime MAY compose a
    sequence of package versions only when every adjacent target supplies a
    migration from the preceding active version." The active source is 1.0.0,
    and the update target 3.0.0 supplies a `$migrations` program keyed ONLY
    "2.0.0" — i.e. from its adjacent predecessor, not directly from 1.0.0.

    Two things are unspecified here:
      - "MAY compose" makes composition optional: a runtime is free NOT to
        chain 1.0.0 -> 2.0.0 -> 3.0.0 even when it could, and reject for lack
        of a direct migration from the exact active source;
      - §20 never says how a runtime obtains the intermediate 2.0.0 definition
        needed to compose (registry, artifact, host-supplied), and this single
        `host_load` provides only the 3.0.0 definition.

    So the outcome is not deducible: a strict runtime rejects (no migration
    keyed to the active source 1.0.0), while a composing runtime that can
    source 2.0.0 MAY accept. Recorded as unspecified; whatever the runtime
    does, 1.0.0 must remain active if it declines (§9.2, §9.4, Annex E.9).
  '''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.mig.compose@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      items: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        name: "text"
      }
      $public: {
        items: { $view: ".items { id, name }" }
      }
    }
    $data: {
      items: { i1: { name: "seed" } }
    }
  }

  steps: [
    { host_load: {
        package: {
          $liasse: 1
          $app: "t.mig.compose@3.0.0"
          $model: {
            items: {
              $key: "id"
              id: "text"
              tag: "text"
            }
            $migrations: {
              // only from the adjacent predecessor 2.0.0, never from 1.0.0
              "2.0.0": [
                ".items = $old.items { id, tag: string.trim(.label) }"
              ]
            }
            $public: {
              items: { $view: ".items { id, tag }" }
            }
          }
        }
      }
      expect: { outcome: unspecified } }
  ]
}
